{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3330639,"name":"Ethan Sanders","username":"essanders","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/essanders/{size}/208157_2.png","created_at":"2024-03-12T00:02:55.739Z","cooked":"<p>We have a differential drivetrain that isn’t following a PathPlanner path correctly. It goes straight fine, going to the right x pose, but the y-axis is quite messed up. The issues seem to come when the robot is turning, messing up the followed path. Our robot knows it is the wrong spot on the field using odometry.</p>
<p>Here are our values from Sysid.<br>
leftKS = 0.0088193 (volts)<br>
leftKV = 0.27474 (volts seconds per meter)<br>
leftKA = 0.077361 (volts seconds squared per meter)<br>
leftP = 0.11574</p>
<p>rightKS = 0.0056672<br>
rightKV = 0.19594<br>
rightKA = 0.056995<br>
rightP = 0.011096<br>
